    <img class='scb_s_homepage_footer_divider' src='images/homepage/small_divider.png'>
    <a href='http://star.mit.edu/about.html'><img class='scb_s_homepage_footer_about'
                                                  src='images/homepage/about_star.png'></a>
    <img class='scb_s_homepage_footer_divider' src='images/homepage/small_divider.png'>
    <a href='http://star.mit.edu/cellbio/support.html'><img class='scb_s_homepage_footer_support'
                                                            src='images/homepage/support.png'></a>
    <button class='save_master_model'>Save</button>
    <button class='load_master_model'>Load</button>

</div>
{/template}

/**
*/
{template .experimental_design_design}
State the objective that the experiment will address your hypothesis for the experiment, and think about the technique that will best suit your experiment.
{/template}

/**
*/
{template .experimental_design_setup}
Specify the strain(s), treatment(s), treatment concentration(s), treatment start time, treatment duration and collection time for your experiment.
{/template}

/**
*/
{template .experimental_design_run_experiment}
Perform your experiment and collect your samples.
{/template}

/**
*/
{template .experimental_design_select_technique}
Select the appropriate experimental technique that is best suited for your experiment.
{/template}

/**
*/
{template .experimental_design_run_technique}
Perform western blotting, flow cytometry and/or microscopy.
{/template}

/**
*/
{template .experimental_design_analyze}
Analyze the results of your experiment.
{/template}

/**
*/
{template .experimental_design_conclude}
Form a conclusion that addresses how your results fit your original hypothesis.
{/template}

